edu.umd.cs.psl.application.groundkernelstore

Interface GroundKernelStore

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Reasoner
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AD3Reasoner, ADMMReasoner, BooleanMaxWalkSat, BooleanMCSat, ConicReasoner, ExecutableReasoner, LatentTopicNetworkADMMReasoner, MemoryGroundKernelStore, UAIFormatReasoner

    public interface GroundKernelStore
    Container for a set of GroundKernels.

    Since this container uses set semantics, no two GroundKernels that are equal can be stored in it. If a Kernel wants to add another GroundKernel that does the same thing over the same GroundAtoms, then it should retrieve the original GroundKernel, modify it, and call changedGroundKernel(GroundKernel).

      • changedGroundKernelWeight

        void changedGroundKernelWeight(GroundCompatibilityKernel gk)
        Notifies this store that a GroundCompatibilityKernel's weight was changed.

        This method should be called whenever the weight of a GroundCompatibilityKernel in this store is changed, or the weight of its parent CompatibilityKernel is changed (and the GroundCompatibilityKernel's weight is still tied to it).

        It is not necessary to also call changedGroundKernel(GroundKernel) if only the weight was changed.

        Parameters:
        gk - the ground kernel with a changed weight
